    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's one of my favorite facts!  I know lots of references for it:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Proposition 9.8 of J.P. May, <em>The geometry of iterated loop spaces</em>, 1972</li>\n<li>Sections 6-7 of Jean-Pierre Meyer. <em>Bar and cobar constructions, I</em>, 1984</li>\n<li>Lemma 6.1.3.16 of Jacob Lurie, <em>Higher topos theory</em>, 2009</li>\n<li>Theorem 5.3.1 of Riehl-Verity, <em>The 2-category theory of quasi-categories</em>, 2015</li>\n<li>Lemma 7.5 of Shulman, <em>All (∞,1)-toposes have strict univalent universes</em>, 2019</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 533915488,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1754980087
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Great, thanks so much! I see you paper even has the part about the free adjunction!</p>",
